metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments:
hah
you thought I forgot all about the Calamity Mod soundtrack, didn't y'all? Well, you're wrong! I was just busy with schoolwork, and I now have the time to release one of the BIG songs! This is the theme for the 'Devourer of Gods,' the big antepenultimate boss of the mod and the #1 god-assimilating space worm minion to the big bad tyrant destroying the world. 
As you can see in bars 9-16, there's a LOT of syncopation to represent the drumbeat. This may or may not be against the rules of the contributor guide, but it's awesome, so I kept it anyway when I charted it around 4 months ago. Consider it foreshadowing to the outtro, too.

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments:
This song has 2 different verses, with dynamic and rhythmic changes, but Hooktheory only supports up to 1 verse and chorus each, so I'll have to fijangle something out there...
But anyway, the Devourer of Gods. Huge space worm, eats gods and steals their powers, plated in awesome armor, doesn't want to shut up whatsoever, and wants to eat you because you killed his minions. This section is relatively basic, introducing the first of his three leitmotifs, and aside from that cool VII7sus4 chord and iim7(add9)-#viio7 movement from relative major there's nothing special about this section.

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments: Changed i9(no5) chords to i7sus2 in measures 3 and 7, and changed B7sus2-%-Amaj7-G#7-F#11-% in measures 9-14 to Dmaj7sus2-%-C#m7-Badd9-F#m7-% respectively (the "%" means repeat measure). Not too certain about that last part, so can someone with better relative pitch please help?

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments: Changed F# to D#m7, D to Dmaj7, and final B to G#m7. I don't know if these changes were made in the Nonstop Mix or part of the original, but just in case.

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments:
Quick note about the previous section: there WERE some differences between the first verse and the second, but there's no way to call it "Verse 2" without breaking the flow of the tab or making Hooktheory upset. Besides, all that changed was the ending, so that's just a run-on of the first, and I'm already breaking a handful of rules, so I don't want it to go TOO far!
As for the bridge, it's a good way to cap off the second chorus, but there's nothing more than that.

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments: First of all: we're in half-time now. I think. So everything's twice as slow. But aside from that, this section introduces the THIRD of the Devourer's three leitmotifs: it's the one used in the intro of the big medley combining his, his minions, and his One-Winged Angel's themes.

metadata.song: Terraria Calamity Mod - Scourge of the Universe
metadata.editComments: Changed Mixolydian B/C# chords to C#m11. They sound the same, but I tended to prioritize the name over function.
